event.title: a decrease of 81 people, or 5.5%, since the 2001

data.event: In the 2006 census 1,398 people are usually resident in Woodville, a decrease of 81 people, or 5.5%, since the 2001 Census.

event.title: years since muttonbirds were last seen

data.event: It is some years since muttonbirds were last seen on this part of the Ruahine Mountains.

event.title: an interview on Radio Woodville in 2009

data.event: According to an interview on Radio Woodville in 2009, the peak of 920 m (2950 ft) gained its name when migrating muttonbird nested on top of the ridges of the Ruahine mountain range.
